# Portfolix SlipGen agent rules

## Architecture
- This is a Next.js App Router + Supabase application. Server actions live in `app/actions/`, Supabase helpers in `utils/supabase/`.
- The client is UNTRUSTED. All payroll computation, validation, and persistence happen server-side. Never accept computed figures (netPay, lopDeduction, deferredClosing, snapshots) from the browser — accept raw inputs only and recompute on the server.
- `lib/payroll-calc.ts` and `lib/amount-in-words.ts` remain dependency-free pure modules and are the ONLY place payroll math exists. Server actions call them; UI renders stored results.
- Fail closed: missing env, failed auth, or a failed guard throws immediately. No mock Supabase clients outside tests.
- Full PAN, bank account number, IFSC, bank name, and work location may be stored and are rendered on the Authorised Slip. The internal Final slip continues to render PAN and account masked. Aadhaar is NEVER collected, stored, or rendered.
- Allowed dependencies now include: @supabase/ssr, @supabase/supabase-js, zod. Do not add other packages without asking.

## Payroll math
- `perDayRate = baseSalary ÷ 25` — the 25-day constant is hardcoded and not editable in the UI.
- Flex bank: `flexAvailable = balance + earned`; `unpaidLate = max(late − flexAvailable, 0)`; LOP-from-lateness = `unpaidLate ÷ 480` **floored to 0.5 day (always favors the employee)**.
- `lopDays = absent + 0.5 × halfDays + LOP-from-lateness`.
- `net = (base + fixedAllowance) − (lopDays × rate + otherDeductions) + variablePaid`, rounded once.
- Deferral is **variable-only**; `deferredClosing > 0` requires a committed payout date before export; the deferred-opening ledger auto-chains from the last FINAL slip.
- `variablePaid ≤ variableEarned + deferredOpening` — reject otherwise.
- All math lives only in `lib/payroll-calc.ts` and `lib/amount-in-words.ts`. UI and stores never re-derive a number.

## Design system
- 60/30/10 tokens in `tailwind.config.ts`: neutrals (`paper`, `surface`, `ink`, `muted`, `hairline`); Inter sans-serif; `emerald-brand` for FINAL slips and net-pay bands; `amber-brand` for DRAFT badges and warnings.
- All monetary figures use `.amount` (tabular nums).
- Slip status classes: `slip-badge-draft`, `slip-badge-final`, `slip-banner-deferred`, `slip-net-band`; amount rows use `.slip-amount-row` (fixed right column).
- A4 slip print output must match the PDF export (`app/globals.css` `@media print`, `198mm` slip width).
- Dates always render as `DD MMM yyyy` via `date-fns` (`lib/format.ts`).

## Workflow
- Tabs: Employee Roster → Generator → History → Settings.
- **Roster**: CRUD employees; flex-bank adjust with mandatory reason (audit log); Excel template download + bulk upload.
- **Generator**: split-screen inputs + live A4 preview; Draft/Final toggle; Print + PDF (`PX_PaySlip_YYYY-MM_<EMPID>[_DRAFT].pdf`); FINAL commits flex balance + deferred ledger; confirm before superseding an existing FINAL for the same employee+month.
- **History**: immutable snapshots — filter by employee/month/status; re-download uses stored snapshot numbers, never recomputed.
- **Settings**: payroll calendar (payday day-of-month 1–31; credit date clamps to month length; query deadline = creditDate − 2 calendar days via `payrollCycleDates` in `lib/format.ts`), payroll contact on every slip, per-entity branding and logo upload.
- **ATTENDANCE CYCLE (founder-ratified 19 Jul 2026):** salary is calculated on the 25th-previous-month → 24th-salary-month cycle ("24th to 24th"). This is company policy, not a default — never change it to calendar month or any other window without an explicit founder instruction.
